{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":903,"text":"(Clicking)"},{"time":7804,"text":"I was born with bilateral retinoblastoma,"},{"time":12420,"text":"retinal cancer."},{"time":15313,"text":"My right eye was removed"},{"time":18419,"text":"at seven months of age."},{"time":21336,"text":"I was 13 months\nwhen they removed my left eye."},{"time":26003,"text":"The first thing I did\nupon awakening from that last surgery"},{"time":31148,"text":"was to climb out of my crib"},{"time":34780,"text":"and begin wandering around\nthe intensive care nursery,"},{"time":39829,"text":"probably looking for the one\nwho did this to me."},{"time":43208,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":46966,"text":"Evidently, wandering around the nursery"},{"time":50127,"text":"was not a problem for me without eyes."},{"time":53702,"text":"The problem was getting caught."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57557,"text":"It's impressions about blindness"},{"time":60731,"text":"that are far more threatening"},{"time":64221,"text":"to blind people than the blindness itself."},{"time":69283,"text":"Think for a moment about\nyour own impressions of blindness."},{"time":73230,"text":"Think about your reactions\nwhen I first came onto the stage,"},{"time":77296,"text":"or the prospect of your own blindness,"},{"time":81347,"text":"or a loved one going blind."},{"time":85264,"text":"The terror is incomprehensible\nto most of us,"},{"time":90704,"text":"because blindness"},{"time":93159,"text":"is thought to epitomize ignorance\nand unawareness,"},{"time":98829,"text":"hapless exposure to the ravages\nof the dark unknown."},{"time":106630,"text":"How poetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109440,"text":"Fortunately for me,\nmy parents were not poetic."},{"time":112801,"text":"They were pragmatic."},{"time":114676,"text":"They understood that ignorance and fear\nwere but matters of the mind,"},{"time":121293,"text":"and the mind is adaptable."},{"time":125282,"text":"They believed that I should grow up"},{"time":128983,"text":"to enjoy the same freedoms\nand responsibilities as everyone else."},{"time":133814,"text":"In their own words, I would move out --"},{"time":136275,"text":"which I did when I was 18 --"},{"time":139062,"text":"I will pay taxes --"},{"time":141035,"text":"thanks --\n(Laughter) --"},{"time":145605,"text":"and they knew the difference\nbetween love and fear."},{"time":150786,"text":"Fear immobilizes us\nin the face of challenge."},{"time":155710,"text":"They knew that blindness\nwould pose a significant challenge."},{"time":158612,"text":"I was not raised with fear."},{"time":161666,"text":"They put my freedom first before all else,"},{"time":165415,"text":"because that is what love does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168535,"text":"Now, moving forward,\nhow do I manage today?"},{"time":174044,"text":"The world is a much larger nursery."},{"time":177419,"text":"Fortunately, I have my trusty long cane,"},{"time":181320,"text":"longer than the canes\nused by most blind people."},{"time":184014,"text":"I call it my freedom staff."},{"time":187357,"text":"It will keep me, for example,"},{"time":188913,"text":"from making an undignified \ndeparture from the stage. (Laughter)"},{"time":195279,"text":"I do see that cliff edge."},{"time":198282,"text":"They warned us earlier\nthat every imaginable mishap"},{"time":201509,"text":"has occurred to speakers\nup here on the stage."},{"time":205100,"text":"I don't care to set a new precedent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208491,"text":"But beyond that,"},{"time":210425,"text":"many of you may have heard me clicking\nas I came onto the stage --"},{"time":213552,"text":"(Clicking) --"},{"time":214619,"text":"with my tongue."},{"time":216488,"text":"Those are flashes of sound"},{"time":219666,"text":"that go out and reflect\nfrom surfaces all around me,"},{"time":224746,"text":"just like a bat's sonar,"},{"time":226118,"text":"and return to me with patterns, \nwith pieces of information,"},{"time":231738,"text":"much as light does for you."},{"time":235135,"text":"And my brain, thanks to my parents,"},{"time":238793,"text":"has been activated to form images\nin my visual cortex,"},{"time":244098,"text":"which we now call the imaging system,"},{"time":247338,"text":"from those patterns of information,\nmuch as your brain does."},{"time":251288,"text":"I call this process flash sonar."},{"time":254604,"text":"It is how I have learned to see\nthrough my blindness,"},{"time":260322,"text":"to navigate my journey"},{"time":263498,"text":"through the dark unknowns\nof my own challenges,"},{"time":267538,"text":"which has earned me the moniker"},{"time":271439,"text":"\"the remarkable Batman.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":275154,"text":"Now, Batman I will accept."},{"time":277708,"text":"Bats are cool. Batman is cool."},{"time":281098,"text":"But I was not raised to think of myself\nas in any way remarkable."},{"time":287856,"text":"I have always regarded myself\nmuch like anyone else"},{"time":291884,"text":"who navigates the dark unknowns\nof their own challenges."},{"time":297300,"text":"Is that so remarkable?"},{"time":300718,"text":"I do not use my eyes, I use my brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304834,"text":"Now, someone, somewhere,"},{"time":307317,"text":"must think that's remarkable,\nor I wouldn't be up here,"},{"time":311144,"text":"but let's consider this for a moment."},{"time":315013,"text":"Everyone out there"},{"time":317739,"text":"who faces or who has ever\nfaced a challenge,"},{"time":322428,"text":"raise your hands."},{"time":325470,"text":"Whoosh. Okay."},{"time":327490,"text":"Lots of hands going up, a moment,\nlet me do a head count."},{"time":330462,"text":"(Clicking)"},{"time":333713,"text":"This will take a while.\n(Clicking) (Laughter)"},{"time":336731,"text":"Okay, lots of hands in the air."},{"time":338205,"text":"Keep them up. I have an idea."},{"time":340609,"text":"Those of you who use your brains\nto navigate these challenges,"},{"time":346302,"text":"put your hands down."},{"time":350423,"text":"Okay, anyone with your hands still up"},{"time":353024,"text":"has challenges of your own. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358262,"text":"So we all face challenges,"},{"time":360839,"text":"and we all face the dark unknown,"},{"time":364577,"text":"which is endemic to most challenges,\nwhich is what most of us fear, okay?"},{"time":368920,"text":"But we all have brains"},{"time":372773,"text":"that allow us, that activate to allow us"},{"time":377069,"text":"to navigate the journey\nthrough these challenges. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384151,"text":"Case in point: I came up here"},{"time":388284,"text":"and -- (Clicking) -- they wouldn't tell me"},{"time":395254,"text":"where the lectern was."},{"time":398152,"text":"So you can't trust those TED folks."},{"time":402796,"text":"\"Find it yourself,\" they said."},{"time":404653,"text":"So -- (Laughter)"},{"time":409413,"text":"And the feedback for the P.A. system\nis no help at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412525,"text":"So now I present to you a challenge."},{"time":415934,"text":"So if you'd all close your eyes\nfor just a moment, okay?"},{"time":419850,"text":"And you're going to learn\na bit of flash sonar."},{"time":423507,"text":"I'm going to make a sound."},{"time":425017,"text":"I'm going to hold this panel in front \nof me, but I'm not going to move it."},{"time":428562,"text":"Just listen to the sound for a moment."},{"time":433236,"text":"Shhhhhhhhhh."},{"time":439228,"text":"Okay, nothing very interesting."},{"time":441293,"text":"Now, listen to what happens\nto that same exact sound"},{"time":444032,"text":"when I move the panel."},{"time":447146,"text":"Shhhhhhhhhhh. \n(Pitch getting higher and lower)"},{"time":458266,"text":"You do not know the power\nof the dark side."},{"time":461609,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":463421,"text":"I couldn't resist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467832,"text":"Okay, now keep your eyes closed"},{"time":470479,"text":"because, did you hear the difference?"},{"time":472327,"text":"Okay. Now, let's be sure."},{"time":475425,"text":"For your challenge,"},{"time":477224,"text":"you tell me, just say \"now\"\nwhen you hear the panel start to move."},{"time":482308,"text":"Okay? We'll relax into this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488160,"text":"Shhhhhhh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491823,"text":"Audience: Now.\nDaniel Kish: Good. Excellent."},{"time":493888,"text":"Open your eyes."},{"time":495381,"text":"All right. So just a few centimeters,"},{"time":499915,"text":"you would notice the difference."},{"time":502045,"text":"You've experienced sonar."},{"time":505528,"text":"You'd all make great blind people.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":508547,"text":"Let's have a look at what can happen"},{"time":511240,"text":"when this activation process"},{"time":514584,"text":"is given some time and attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519111,"text":"(Video) Juan Ruiz: It's like\nyou guys can see with your eyes"},{"time":522292,"text":"and we can see with our ears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525497,"text":"Brian Bushway: It's not a matter\nof enjoying it more or less,"},{"time":528561,"text":"it's about enjoying it differently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531487,"text":"Shawn Marsolais: It goes across.\nDK: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534529,"text":"SM: And then it's gradually\ncoming back down again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538337,"text":"DK: Yes!\nSM: That's amazing."},{"time":539950,"text":"I can, like, see the car. Holy mother!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549981,"text":"J. Louchart: I love being blind."},{"time":552048,"text":"If I had the opportunity, honestly,\nI wouldn't go back to being sighted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555716,"text":"JR: The bigger the goal,\nthe more obstacles you'll face,"},{"time":559176,"text":"and on the other side of that goal"},{"time":561777,"text":"is victory."},{"time":563425,"text":"[In Italian]"},{"time":568580,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578355,"text":"DK: Now, do these people look terrified?"},{"time":582245,"text":"Not so much."},{"time":584067,"text":"We have delivered activation training"},{"time":586853,"text":"to tens of thousands of blind\nand sighted people from all backgrounds"},{"time":590382,"text":"in nearly 40 countries."},{"time":592820,"text":"When blind people learn to see,"},{"time":597302,"text":"sighted people seem inspired"},{"time":600320,"text":"to want to learn to see their way\nbetter, more clearly, with less fear,"},{"time":606627,"text":"because this exemplifies\nthe immense capacity within us all"},{"time":612533,"text":"to navigate any type of challenge,\nthrough any form of darkness,"},{"time":619046,"text":"to discoveries unimagined"},{"time":622332,"text":"when we are activated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627695,"text":"I wish you all a most activating journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633709,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635474,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643716,"text":"Chris Anderson: Daniel, my friend."},{"time":646162,"text":"As I know you can see, it's\na spectacular standing ovation at TED."},{"time":651297,"text":"Thank you for an extraordinary talk."},{"time":654281,"text":"Just one more question about your world,\nyour inner world that you construct."},{"time":659530,"text":"We think that we have things in our world\nthat you as a blind person don't have,"},{"time":665095,"text":"but what's your world like?"},{"time":666819,"text":"What do you have that we don't have?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669582,"text":"DK: Three hundred and sixty-degree view,"},{"time":672717,"text":"so my sonar works about as well\nbehind me as it does in front of me."},{"time":676618,"text":"It works around corners."},{"time":678499,"text":"It works through surfaces."},{"time":682448,"text":"Generally, it's kind of a fuzzy\nthree-dimensional geometry."},{"time":687229,"text":"One of my students, who has now\nbecome an instructor,"},{"time":691269,"text":"when he lost his vision,\nafter a few months"},{"time":694195,"text":"he was sitting in his three story house"},{"time":696447,"text":"and he realized that he could hear\neverything going on throughout the house:"},{"time":700464,"text":"conversations, people in the kitchen,\npeople in the bathroom,"},{"time":704643,"text":"several floors away, several walls away."},{"time":707337,"text":"He said it was something\nlike having x-ray vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710889,"text":"CA: What do you picture\nthat you're in right now?"},{"time":714511,"text":"How do you picture this theater?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717530,"text":"DK: Lots of loudspeakers, quite frankly."},{"time":724453,"text":"It's interesting. \nWhen people make a sound,"},{"time":728709,"text":"when they laugh, when they fidget,\nwhen they take a drink or blow their nose"},{"time":733864,"text":"or whatever, I hear everything."},{"time":736557,"text":"I hear every little movement\nthat every single person makes."},{"time":739738,"text":"None of it really escapes my attention,"},{"time":742501,"text":"and then, from a sonar perspective,"},{"time":744355,"text":"the size of the room, the curvature \nof the audience around the stage,"},{"time":750209,"text":"it's the height of the room."},{"time":753847,"text":"Like I say, it's all that kind \nof three-dimensional surface geometry"},{"time":757127,"text":"all around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758544,"text":"CA: Well, Daniel, you have done\na spectacular job"},{"time":760830,"text":"of helping us all see the world\nin a different way."},{"time":763655,"text":"Thanks so much for that, truly.\nDK: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765825,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}